The 39A has been in continuous production longer than any other rifle in America and is often referred to as the cadillac of 22 rifles. The Marlin lever action’s swift pointing characteristics, lightning-fast follow-ups, reliability and inherent accuracy have made it America’s favorite. And what started with the invention of the first flat-top, side-eject receiver in 1889 has led Marlin to pioneer every major advancement in the lever-action category since. The Golden 39A is still considered one of the finest examples of a lever .22 rifle, and one of the most accurate .22 rifles ever produced. It is also the best-selling lever rimfire in U.S. history. The 39A and the AS are the same rifles, the AS designation the S was added in 1988 because Marlin added a hammer block safety and a rebounding hammer.

W.A.S.P. Treated Barrel
(Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied to the barrel inside and out, along with the front sight base on our LE rifles and uppers. Nitriding offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance when compared to hard chrome lining or phosphating. 

Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitriding converts the surface without the risk of dimensional build up. CMMG Pioneered the use of this nitriding process on AR barrels and has been using it for many years.

title: For Sale:  SOLD -  LNIB M48 Yugo Mauser Sniper 8mm with Zrak Mounts installed
postcontent:
Up for sale is a near mint Yugo M48 sniper. This is the M48 with all milled parts. The rifle was a hand pick from an unfired bunch (excluding factory testing of course) and was de-cosmolined by me. The rifle has a total of 25 rounds through it all match or sniper ammo.

There have been a number of questions about the work that was done to the rifle so I will explain it in more detail

The rifle was brand new, unfired, handpicked.

The Zrak mounts are genuine from the factory 

To mount them properly is not simply a matter of drilling holes, the rear base needs to be milled to tailor it to the contour of the receiver where it curves upward to become the stripper clip guide. It is cheaper and easier to simply grind off that portion of the receiver for the mount, but it does not look nearly as nice. 

Next the bolt was turned down and the stock relieved so that the bolt locks down and fits flush. The finish was then matched so that there is no major irregularity in color 

Sure one could save money cutting corners, but this was not just a thrown together hack job. This was a professionally done rifle. 

The wood on the rifle is excellent with only minor surface dings. It is the prettier dark grain. 

The finish on the metal is near perfect as seen in the photos. The only blemish is that the buttplate could stand to be polished. 

The bore and internals are mint. The rifle was thoroughly cleaned after each session. The barrel itself is bright and shiny a la new rifle. The lines from when the bore was cut are still present.

Overall this is an excellent example of a firearm with all the professional work done to it. It was not a nice used gun, it was bought brand new out of the box. I am only selling because I have decided to move into the German Mauser Realm.

Scope not included.

title: For Sale:  Camo PASGT helmet with surefire helmet light
postcontent:
Keep your dome from being blasted off when the zombies learn how to shoot back!  Selling a PASGT helmet with surefire helmet light.  It has been painted with a simple OD green and tan camo pattern.  Includes an unused spare head band.  Missing chin strap but has all the needed hardware for it.  The helmet light itself is very expensive, but I'll take $50 for everything.  

This is a real kevlar ballistic helmet, not some fake air soft toy.  Most pistol bullets, and glancing rifle rounds in some cases will not penetrate it.  Think of it as in a nutshell level IIIa protection.  This was military issue for a long time until recently.  (This exact helmet has been worn in the war on terror)  The new helmets issued simply have the lip on the front of the helmet removed, there is a hole drilled for mounting night vision, and there are pads inside the helmet rather than a suspension system like this older PASGT.    When the zombies start weilding 9's, .40's, .45's, .38's, .357's, .380's and frag grenades,this will do a great job of guarding your noggin.  For 50 bucks, you can have a bullet resistant brain!  Take that, zombie Rambo!

Disclaimer: please don't shoot yourself in the head to try this helmet out, unless you are hopelessly liberal, or are a staunch believer in Darwainism.  For real though...  Don't do it.  Even though it may stop the round,  it won't stop the energy transfer.  You might as well smack yourself in the forehead with a mallet.  Ps: don't do that either.

title: For Sale:  U.S. L.F.&C 1917 Knuckle Duster Trench Knife
postcontent: This near mint condition 1917 Trench Knife was a G.I. bring back.  The blade is a triangular shaped spike designed to be able to penetrate heavy battle gear and to create a wound that would not close.  Combined with the pyramid shaped knuckle duster hand gaurd this was a devastating weapon meant for close hand to hand combat.  I researched information on the knife and discovered it was only produced for just over one year.  The military then switched to a standard blade fighting knife.  These are rare to come by and have seen them auction for $750.+.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson M&P 40 Customized by Robar
postcontent:
S&W M&P 40 Customized By Robar! In .40 S&W Caliber Shooting Industry Masters Auction Benefiting First Shots More than 350 industry representatives, ranging from top administrators and factory personnel to professional shooters, will compete in the 2013 Shooting Industry Masters shooting competition July 19-20 at the Cody Shooting Complex near Cody, Wyoming. A major component of the shoot will be fundraising events to benefit the National Shooting Sports Foundation (NSSF) First Shots program, which introduces thousands of new shooters to the shooting sports each year. The Robar Companies have been customizing and finishing firearms for decades, and have developed a world-wide reputation for craftsmanship, customer service and aerospace-grade metal finishes. Robar uses their same high-tech plating process used on space vehicles and demanding industry applications, to create custom finishes on firearms that can withstand any extreme you could ever encounter. 
NP3+ (applied to the metal parts of this custom gun) has five times the ability to withstand corrosion as the original NP3, and up to ten times more resistance than regular nickel. 
Benefits of NP3+ are: EXTREMELY CORROSION RESISTANT: A 1mil (.001) thick coating of can withstand a salt spray corrosion test of 1,000+ hours per ASTM B-117 SELF-LUBRICATING: PTFE is deposited throughout the coating so for most firearms no additional lubrication is needed after initial break-in. ACCURATE PLATING THICKNESS: Coating thickness can be predetermined for nominal tolerance to suit your weapon system. VERY ABRASION RESISTANT: NP3 Plus is a very hard, abrasion-resistant coating with an as-plated hardness of Rc 35-50. In certain applications it can be heat treated to Rc 68-70 EASY TO CLEAN: NP3 Plus is easy to clean; in most cases wiping with a rag will suffice (We do NOT plate the inside of barrels; these need to be cleaned conventionally). LONGER FIRING PERIODS: NP3 Plus allows for longer firing 
cycles as the dry, self-lubricating PTFE-rich surface makes it harder for powder residue and debris to adhere to surfaces PLATES TO MOST GUN ALLOYS: NP3 Plus can be plated to almost all alloys used in the firearms industry. This includes steel, aluminum and stainless steel. SERVICE LIFE IS EXTENDED: NP3 Plus has a high lubricity and low coefficient of friction; therefore, the life expectancy of a firearm will be greatly increased due to less frictional wear. NO COROSSION MIGRATION: In cases where the coating is damaged and perforated, the corrosion shows no tendency to spread or migrate under the coating. EASY TO REPLATE: NP3 Plus is chemically strippable and can be re-plated without any damage to the substrate. Weapons subject to heavy use can be refurbished to as-new condition.
